OL,3,CWorkplaces must change attitudes to
OL,4,Cneurodiversity, says chef Heston
OL,5,CBlumenthal
OL,7,FBlumenthal believes more needs to be
OL,8,Fdone to welcome neurodivergent
OL,9,Findividuals in the workplace and said
OL,10,Fthey are "woefully underrepresented"
OL,11,Fas a result.
OL,13,F"These are individuals who may have
OL,14,Fexceptional skills and unparalleled
OL,15,Fabilities yet because of traditional
OL,16,Fways of working, we are missing out on
OL,17,Fthe brilliance they can bring to UK
OL,18,Fbusiness," he said.
