OL,3,CWorkplaces must change attitudes to
OL,4,Cneurodiversity, says chef Heston
OL,5,CBlumenthal
OL,7,F"I hope that being open about my own
OL,8,Fmental health will raise awareness of
OL,9,Fthe issue and I want to campaign to
OL,10,Fhighlight the contribution
OL,11,Fneurodiversity can make to the
OL,12,Fworkplace."
OL,14,FBlumenthal commissioned research which
OL,15,Ffound more than one in 10 people (11%)
OL,16,Fsurveyed have been officially
OL,17,Fdiagnosed as neurodivergent. Around
OL,18,F21% of these were neither in full nor
OL,19,Fpart-time paid employment.
