OL,3,CWorkplaces must change attitudes to
OL,4,Cneurodiversity, says chef Heston
OL,5,CBlumenthal
OL,7,FSinead Devine-French, chief science
OL,8,Fofficer of The Positive Group, said:
OL,9,F"Embracing neurodiversity in the
OL,10,Fworkplace isn't just a nice-to-have `
OL,11,Fit can be a strategic game-changer.
OL,13,F"Recognising that every individual
OL,14,Fbrings a unique blend of strengths,
OL,15,Fcognitive experiences and perspectives
OL,16,Fenriches our thinking and propels our
OL,17,Fcreativity.
